718856f-c.title: Manhattan: Church Street - Cortlandt Street
718856f-c.text:
(1)
Church Street, east side, north from and including Cortlandt
to and including Vesey Streets. The view shows razing sd
the Haveneyer Building. The Sixth Ave., ''L'' is shown on
CChurch Street, and obstructing the view of the street level.
November 7, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, north to and including Dey Street.
November 7, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(3)
The same as No. 2, from a slightly different angel.
November 7, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPPODUCTIONS.

718855f-a.title: Manhattan: Church Street - Cortlandt Street
718855f-a.text:
Church Street (elevated line thereon), east side, north from Cort-
landt Street (station) to Fulton Street and showing an excavation where
the former 15-story Havemeyer Building stood. The East River Savings
Bank will erect a 1-story banking structure on this site. The new
2-story building seen north of same,is occupied as a retail store by
F. W. Woolworth \& Co.
March 5, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
